ned>Faned</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kentmbrown.com/PDF/cubed.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#333333>(12/7/02 9:18:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=393.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kentmbrown.com/PDF/Faned_pulling.gif w=90 h=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:</span><hr size=1> I think magician pets are fine.  They are fairly well balanced against the damage dealing of monks/rogues/rangers.  They are very well balanced against the tanking of warriors/SKs/paladins.<br>
<br>
However, the fact that they can apparently tank better than a monk *while* magician + pet puts out more damage is far from balanced.  Since they are balanced well against all other classes, it's not hard to figure out where the problem is.<br>
<br>
Sony has a 6-sided die with &quot;nerf&quot; on 5 sides.  Roll dem bones.<br>
<br>
And yeah, I conceded his point.  As long as you concede mine that clerics can put out 30-250% of the damage of magicians.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
