<br>
1) pets cannot easily pull aggro from adds which are causing problems (say interupting a clerics casts?)<br>
<br>
2) pets cannot easily position mobs (ever have a mob poof up on a wall?)<br>
<br>
3) if pets are tanking, that means your group cant have any other melee as it can no longer tank. this severely limits potential group members to other pet classes and wizards.<br>
<br>
4) if there are no melee that means one of the casters must pull. that means one of the casters (probably the magician) is losing alot of dps, since during what is supposed to be &quot;downtime&quot; they are moving around instead of medding. the magician equivilant of a monk whos dps is rivaled by an air pet needs all the downtime they can get. their nuking dps will be very low.<br>
<br>
5) if while pulling the magician gets an add they have no choice but to bring them both, whereas a monk can feign split.<br>
<br>
Like i asked lordofkaos over on the monk board tell me faned what group do you think is getting better exp, a group with a magician pet tank or a group with a monk tank?  <br>
<br>
please this is ridiculous. &quot;oh no magician pets out tank monks&quot; lol give me a break... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A> at: 12/7/02 4:01:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faned>Faned</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kentmbrown.com/PDF/cubed.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#333333>(12/8/02 2:17:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=393.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.kentmbrown.com/PDF/Faned_pulling.gif w=90 h=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Faned, Just to clear things up</span><hr size=1> Ya know, I went ahead and got level 61 with my magician.  Figured if I want to solo I'll drop all the way down to my level 11 beastlord.  :P<br>
<br>
Anyway, I also got my magician flagged for PoV yesterday and went and joined a group in &quot;inner cave&quot; (at 60 at the time, hit 61 in there).  I have the bolt spell, that's it (still, /rude Sony).<br>
<br>
We had a pull go bad, cleric died, enchanter died, three mobs in camp.  We decide to run.  Everybody runs, my pet obviously stays there mindlessly beating on mobs.<br>
<br>
I don't know whether one mob stayed or two or all three.  I do know that at least one did because the pet's health was going down the whole time and it eventually died.  When I got to the zoneout stone, my pet was still alive, though not by much.  I stood there and waited for it to die before zoning.  In the time elapsed, as Faned I would have been Feigned (or dead) by then.<br>
<br>
I'm looking forward to getting the level 61 pet to run some real tests.<br>
<br>
And to address a few things:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>magician pets are by design hard to control, to prevent mage pets from ever becomming effective tanks<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A) They're not all that hard to control, particularly these days.<br>
B) If a magician pet is tanking, there are no other melees.  It's not hard to adjust for whatever mob the magician pet picks to tank.<br>
C) If there are no other melees, you will probably be trying to fight single mobs most of the time anyway so it's a non-issue.<br>
<br>
Yeah, magician pets have some downsides.  No other melees is a huge one, but hey, just get more pets.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>pets cannot easily pull aggro from adds which are causing problems<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And yet, better than a monk...  Ask a warrior how hard it is to &quot;back up&quot; or position a mob while a pet is beating on it.  I watched it last night.  If the warrior, who has *solid* aggro tries to move back to get the mob to follow him and gets out of melee range, the mob just turns onto the pet.  I've always wondered about people who complain about magician pets having poor aggro, I think they're the same people that insist on standing in melee range and wondering why the mob isn't hitting the pet instead of them.<br>
<br>
I agree that pets are pretty bad at positioning mobs.  Particularly if they're the only tank/melee in the group.  But really, so are most warriors (and they don't have any excuse  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
Last night, with a melee in the group, the enchanter was pulling.  It kept the mobs coming in a steady stream.  If a melee runs off before the mob dies to pull something else...  whaddya know, DPS suffers...<br>
<br>
From *tons* of experience.  In exp grinds I can go <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>hours</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and even whole evenings without ever needing to feign.  Yes, feign is amazingly awesomely cool.  But if you've got any intelligence and experience pulling it's very seldom required.  This is even more the case in PoP outdoor zones.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Very</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> few things need split.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>what group do you think is getting better exp, a group with a magician pet tank or a group with a monk tank?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't think either one will be doing all that great.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   As to which would do better...  I don't know yet.  The fact that I don't know is a problem.  The answer should be clear.<br>
