<br>
The way people advance in EQ is like this:<br>
1) they advance through getting AA and lvl(skill).<br>
2) they advance through sarcificing some time to get money or doing a quest or join a guild to advance through gear. <br>
<br>
Missing either one is stupid.  If you are saying you get your monk to 61(?) and you didn't spend the same time as some other monks to get gear, of course you monk is going to suck and it's not even a surprise that a air pet can solo you in a duel. <br>
